<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1325,398,1785]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,457,758,784]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Description</emphasis>
. Massive, irregular but slightly lobate, internally cavernous (
<figureCitation box="[1210,1286,759,785]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[264,368,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[300,1307,283,1709]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[300,1309,274,1711]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Biemna spinomicroxea sp. n. (Holotype, MCNPOR 1887). A. Specimen preserved in alcohol (scale bar = 0.5 cm); B. Skeletal arrangement (scale bar = 300 µm); C. Oxea (scale bar = 100 µm); D. Detail of oxea extremities (scale bar = 10 µm); E. Spiny sigma (scale bar = 5 µm); F. Detail of sigma extremity (scale bar = 2 µm); G. Microxea I (scale bar = 20 µm); H. Detail of microxea I extremity (scale bar = 2 µm); I. Microxea II (scale bar = 20 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170498/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number box="[1270,1286,759,785]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Measurements: 
<quantity box="[454,539,799,825]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" unit="cm" value="3.5">3.5 cm</quantity>
length, 2.0 cm width and 2.0 cm thick. Surface hispid, from to protruding spicules. Oscules scattered over the surface, the larger ones measuring 
<quantity box="[1241,1323,839,865]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" unit="cm" value="0.2">0.2 cm</quantity>
in diameter. Consistency of preserved material soft, easily compressible. Colour alive unknown, in alcohol light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1325,398,1785]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,420,958,984]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Skeleton</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[435,505,959,985]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[264,368,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[300,1307,283,1709]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[300,1309,274,1711]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Biemna spinomicroxea sp. n. (Holotype, MCNPOR 1887). A. Specimen preserved in alcohol (scale bar = 0.5 cm); B. Skeletal arrangement (scale bar = 300 µm); C. Oxea (scale bar = 100 µm); D. Detail of oxea extremities (scale bar = 10 µm); E. Spiny sigma (scale bar = 5 µm); F. Detail of sigma extremity (scale bar = 2 µm); G. Microxea I (scale bar = 20 µm); H. Detail of microxea I extremity (scale bar = 2 µm); I. Microxea II (scale bar = 20 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170498/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number box="[489,505,959,985]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Plumoreticulate, not differentiated into ectosomal or choanosomal skeleton. Megascleres arranged in ascending tracts, 
<number box="[885,930,999,1025]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
spicules thick, at 
<quantity box="[1149,1323,999,1025]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6125" metricValueMax="3.325" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" unit="m" value="261.25" valueMax="332.5" valueMin="190.0">190–332.5 m</quantity>
distance from each other, widening slightly near the surface and connected by single spicules or transverse tracts 
<number box="[600,645,1079,1105]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
spicules thick. Only nodal spongin present. Between the spicule tracts, some microscleres are found randomly distributed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1325,398,1785]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,414,1158,1184]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Spicules</emphasis>
. Oxeas (
<figureCitation box="[535,613,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[264,368,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[300,1307,283,1709]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[300,1309,274,1711]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Biemna spinomicroxea sp. n. (Holotype, MCNPOR 1887). A. Specimen preserved in alcohol (scale bar = 0.5 cm); B. Skeletal arrangement (scale bar = 300 µm); C. Oxea (scale bar = 100 µm); D. Detail of oxea extremities (scale bar = 10 µm); E. Spiny sigma (scale bar = 5 µm); F. Detail of sigma extremity (scale bar = 2 µm); G. Microxea I (scale bar = 20 µm); H. Detail of microxea I extremity (scale bar = 2 µm); I. Microxea II (scale bar = 20 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170498/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number box="[598,613,1159,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C­D): slightly curved, rarely straight; extremities lightly stepped, a few slightly strongylote; length: 
<number box="[795,941,1199,1225]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="389.95" valueMax="409.4" valueMin="370.5">
370.5– 
<emphasis box="[876,920,1199,1224]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">409</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[927,941,1199,1224]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">4</emphasis>
</number>
– 
<quantity box="[956,1053,1199,1225]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.37" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" unit="m" value="437.0">437 m</quantity>
, width: 
<number box="[1156,1256,1199,1225]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="10.399999999999999" valueMax="11.6" valueMin="9.2">
9.2– 
<emphasis box="[1207,1232,1199,1224]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">11</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1242,1256,1199,1224]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">6</emphasis>
</number>
– 
<quantity metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.38" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" unit="m" value="13.8">13.8 m</quantity>
. Sigmas (
<figureCitation box="[420,490,1239,1265]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[264,368,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[300,1307,283,1709]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[300,1309,274,1711]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Biemna spinomicroxea sp. n. (Holotype, MCNPOR 1887). A. Specimen preserved in alcohol (scale bar = 0.5 cm); B. Skeletal arrangement (scale bar = 300 µm); C. Oxea (scale bar = 100 µm); D. Detail of oxea extremities (scale bar = 10 µm); E. Spiny sigma (scale bar = 5 µm); F. Detail of sigma extremity (scale bar = 2 µm); G. Microxea I (scale bar = 20 µm); H. Detail of microxea I extremity (scale bar = 2 µm); I. Microxea II (scale bar = 20 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170498/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number box="[475,490,1239,1265]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
E­F): shallow­curved, with long­spined extremities; length: 
<number box="[1191,1307,1239,1265]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="16.85" valueMax="17.6" valueMin="16.1">
16.1– 
<emphasis box="[1257,1286,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">17</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1293,1307,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">6</emphasis>
</number>
– 
<quantity box="[264,366,1279,1305]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.07" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" unit="m" value="20.7">20.7 m</quantity>
, width: 1.0 m. Microxeas in two sizes (
<figureCitation box="[855,926,1279,1305]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[264,368,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[300,1307,283,1709]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[300,1309,274,1711]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Biemna spinomicroxea sp. n. (Holotype, MCNPOR 1887). A. Specimen preserved in alcohol (scale bar = 0.5 cm); B. Skeletal arrangement (scale bar = 300 µm); C. Oxea (scale bar = 100 µm); D. Detail of oxea extremities (scale bar = 10 µm); E. Spiny sigma (scale bar = 5 µm); F. Detail of sigma extremity (scale bar = 2 µm); G. Microxea I (scale bar = 20 µm); H. Detail of microxea I extremity (scale bar = 2 µm); I. Microxea II (scale bar = 20 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170498/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number box="[911,926,1279,1305]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
G­I): larger (
<figureCitation box="[1078,1150,1279,1305]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[264,368,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[300,1307,283,1709]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[300,1309,274,1711]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Biemna spinomicroxea sp. n. (Holotype, MCNPOR 1887). A. Specimen preserved in alcohol (scale bar = 0.5 cm); B. Skeletal arrangement (scale bar = 300 µm); C. Oxea (scale bar = 100 µm); D. Detail of oxea extremities (scale bar = 10 µm); E. Spiny sigma (scale bar = 5 µm); F. Detail of sigma extremity (scale bar = 2 µm); G. Microxea I (scale bar = 20 µm); H. Detail of microxea I extremity (scale bar = 2 µm); I. Microxea II (scale bar = 20 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170498/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number box="[1135,1150,1279,1305]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
G­H), straight, microspined; length: 
<number box="[530,654,1319,1345]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="118.2" valueMax="133.4" valueMin="103.0">
103– 
<emphasis box="[589,633,1319,1344]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">133</emphasis>
. 
